Sentencas: The goal of this work is to identify suitable cathode contact materials (CCM) to bond and electrically connect LSCF cathode to Mn1.5Co1.5O4-coated 441 stainless steel after sintering at the relatively low temperature of 900-1000 degrees C. A wide variety of CCM candidates are synthesized and characterized.
Titulo: Selection of cathode contact materials for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: For each, the conductivity, coefficient of thermal expansion, sintering behavior, and tendency to react with LSCF or Mn1.5Co1.5O4 are determined.
Titulo: Selection of cathode contact materials for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: From this screening, LSCF, LSCuF, LSC, and SSC are selected as the most promising candidates.
Titulo: Selection of cathode contact materials for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: These compositions are applied to LSCF and Mn1.5Co1.5O4-coated 441 stainless steel coupons and subjected to 200 h ASR testing at 800 degrees C. After area-specific resistance testing, the specimens are cross-sectioned and analyzed for interdiffusion across the CCM/LSCF or CCM/Mn1.5Co1.5O4 interfaces.
Titulo: Selection of cathode contact materials for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: A relatively narrow band of interdiffusion is observed.
Titulo: Selection of cathode contact materials for solid oxide fuel cells
